<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="701" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/175.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 29, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>398. Department’s 332, September 28. War Office now asks for family
                            history Ajello, which Embassy obtaining from him at Naples. In
                            presenting information desired, will make another urgent appeal for his
                            release.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy.</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>